In [[1964]], [[J.R.R. Tolkien]] wrote '''[[Letters not published in The Letters of J.R.R. Tolkien|a letter]] to Elizabeth Joan Jennings''', the daughter of Tolkien's friend [[Henry Cecil Jennings]].<ref>{{webcite|author=|articleurl=https://historical.ha.com/itm/books/literature-1900-up/j-r-r-tolkien-tree-and-leaf/a/6300-45343.s#|articlename=J. R. R. Tolkien. Tree and Leaf. London: George Allen & Unwin LTD, [1964]|dated=|website=Heritage Auctions|accessed=}}</ref>

* '''Subject:''' An autograph note on a first edition of ''[[Tree and Leaf]]''.

==Transcription==
{{blockquote|Dear Elizabeth,<br>Very best wishes.<br>I hope you have some<br>cheer at [[Christmas]].<br><br>Remember me to [[Wikipedia:Cecil Day-Lewis|C. D. L.]]<br>I believe I have only once<br>met him and wish it<br>were more often.<br><br>Yours ever affectionately,<br>Ronald}}

